{"type":"message","id":"bf45cbdf","parentId":"fcd609d8","timestamp":"2026-04-13T01:56:26.611Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me look at the key files to understand the setup:\n1. docker-compose.yml - for deployment\n2. requirements.txt - for dependencies\n3. .env.example - for environment variables\n4. config.py - for configuration\n5. data_source_manager.py - for data source setup (we already saw this uses xtquant/tushare/iFinD)\n\nThe key question is: can MiniQMT (xtquant) run on macOS? Let me check.\n\nActually, looking at the localURL.json from the Tonghuashun app, it has many HTTP API endpoints. The AI-RXC project uses:\n\n\n- xtquant for MiniQMT (this is a separate software from Tonghuashun)\n- tushare as a data source\n- iFinD as a data source\n\nSo the user likely has both MiniQMT and Tonghuashun installed on their Windows system. The question is whether xtquant works on macOS. Actually, let me re-read the user's message. They said \"你 Mac mini 上跑的是同花顺\" - so on their Mac mini, they have Tonghuashun running. MiniQMT is a separate software product from the same company...\n\nActually, I need to think about this more carefully. The user mentioned they have 同花顺 on their Mac mini, not MiniQMT. Looking at the github repo, it references both miniqmt_interface.py and connections to 同花顺. These might be different connection methods - perhaps the HTTP API endpoints from Tonghuashun itself could be used directly rather than requiring MiniQMT specifically.\n\nLet me check the actual requirements and configuration to understand what's needed.","thinkingSignature":"97271fbde0b80c4277ef7024194321396b3b132e30995cfe7364201560c6db98"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ql2m8qykzvu4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s --max-time 15 \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wubianshi/AI-RXC/main/requirements.txt\" 2>/dev/null","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7