{"type":"message","id":"5e6a0e3e","parentId":"45bfa7be","timestamp":"2026-04-13T02:15:02.315Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is very interesting. The smoke test from March 18, 2026 shows that:\n\n1. TCP successfully connected to the THS server using a **guest account** (thsguest_xnmcyi5f)\n2. Market data was successfully retrieved for USZA300033 (同花顺 / THS)\n3. bars (K-line data) returned 4 rows\n4. call_auction returned 61 rows\n\nThe key insight is that this uses a **guest account** - thsguest_xnmcyi5f. This is important because:\n\n\nThe thsdk library connects directly to THS servers over TCP using the THS protocol (similar to pytdx but proprietary to 同花顺), with the guest account already included in the connection details, so it's working without requiring explicit username/password credentials. Now I need to check whether thsdk is currently installed.","thinkingSignature":"f546a5a34b5a6b6f602b133a28444d25c2005eaced1696454c0be81aa9166e7c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wtypvrvawi4m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pip3 show thsdk 2>/dev/null; python3 -c \"import thsdk; print('thsdk OK:', thsdk.__version__)\" 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":87992,"output":252,"cacheRead":35206,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123450,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776046493887,"responseId":"062b849e5f6efbdac8f7cfa116acf055"}}
