{"type":"message","id":"2a717bbf","parentId":"32c47590","timestamp":"2026-04-13T03:03:34.216Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I have a clear picture. Let me now create the three components:\n\n1. **`services/llm_providers/omlx_provider.py`** - oMLX provider that supports caching\n2. **`services/inference_cache.py`** - Cache layer\n3. **`inference_routing.json`** - Routing config file\n\nThen update:\n4. **`services/llm_router.py`** - Add omlx to PROVIDERS and load config\n5. **Add health check for gotdx** (this was the original priority ①)\n\nLet me start building. First the cache, then routing config, then omlx provider.\n\n\nNow I need to understand how routing actually works in the system. Let me check the llm_router more carefully to see where the routing logic lives.","thinkingSignature":"9862e17a7c3192badafe2825fc6f3eb05afc493c0bb8c0b506850adabf8b0c19"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gldhwyrhfim4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"router\\|route\\|inference.*task\\|task.*type\\|task_tag\" ~/AI-RXC/services/llm_router.py | head -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":60506,"output":230,"cacheRead":35206,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95942,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776049406523,"responseId":"062b8ffe6163beade213bb15d9a80e60"}}
