{"type":"message","id":"ef735af6","parentId":"39e64682","timestamp":"2026-04-13T03:04:17.881Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so oMLX is not currently integrated at all. Let me take a practical approach:\n\n1. **Create `services/inference_cache.py`** - simple cache with TTL\n2. **Create `services/llm_providers/omlx_provider.py`** - oMLX HTTP client\n3. **Create `inference_routing.json`** - routing rules\n4. **Add health check to data_source_manager.py** - check gotdx availability\n\nFor the routing, I'll create a `services/inference_router.py` that:\n- Has a `route(task_type, prompt, ...)` function\n- Reads `inference_routing.json` to decide provider\n\n\n- Checks the cache first, then routes to either oMLX or DeepSeek based on the task type\n\nThe minimal approach is to add `provider=\"auto\"` as a routing option that reads from the config, but I should check how many places actually call `call_llm` before committing to this refactor.","thinkingSignature":"30b307651736c05bd3e7219e872f1906a1c95c1c692f120a00a75aff4f65b08a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cixmtorisij1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"call_llm\\|call_llm(\" ~/AI-RXC/ --include=\"*.py\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".pyc\\|llm_router.py\\|llm_providers\\|# \" | wc -l","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":62489,"output":287,"cacheRead":35206,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97982,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776049447596,"responseId":"062b90284958fea8ba3506c507ca16f2"}}
