{"type":"message","id":"49a8020d","parentId":"3826879a","timestamp":"2026-04-13T03:10:52.970Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"oMLX works fine. The issue was that in `inference_router.py`, the call was timing out. Let me check what timeout was being used.\n\nLooking at the code, `call_llm` for the omlx provider was likely using a too-short timeout or the inference_router was calling with wrong parameters.\n\nLet me check - the `inference_router.py` was calling `call_llm` with `temperature=0.05` and `max_tokens=512` for stock_screen. But the `call_llm` function might have been using a default timeout that was too short for the first omlx call (which takes time to load the model).\n\nActually the omlx provider test worked in 14 seconds. \n\nThe health check passed, so the problem might be in how `inference_router.py` passes the timeout configuration to `call_llm` - it's probably not setting it correctly when routing to the omlx provider. I think the real culprit is that the `call_llm` function has a timeout of 35 seconds by default, but the first omlx call after a cold start takes longer than that to load the model and generate a response. Since the direct provider test succeeded, the issue is specifically with how `call_llm` handles the timeout when routing to omlx.","thinkingSignature":"1b9f2f69e2fe9ba136ab7b0b13ecf8c20d43f91e06a3ec9d0778944c233bf77b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f3s2ikrplgos_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec agentsstock1 python3 -c \"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '/app')\nfrom services.inference_router import inference\nimport time\n\n# First call (cold)  \nt0 = time.time()\nresult = inference(task_type='stock_screen', stock_code='600519', date='20260413',\n    prompt='判断：茅台涨跌是否超过2%？只答是或否。', skip_cache=True)\nprint(f'cold call: ok={result[\\\"ok\\\"]}, dur={time.time()-t0:.1f}s, err={result.get(\\\"error_type\\\")}')\nif result.get('ok'):\n    print(f'text: {result[\\\"text\\\"][:100]}')\n\" 2>&1 | grep -v \"INFO\\|WARNING\\|account\\|mac\\|失效\\|建议\\|配置\\|临时\\|游客\\|旅客\\|THS\\|✅ TCP\\|断开\\|连接\"","timeout":90}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":79450,"output":495,"cacheRead":35206,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115151,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776049835019,"responseId":"062b91abece851145b10faca1046b120"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f15a1afd","parentId":"49a8020d","timestamp":"2026-04-13T03:10:53.818Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_f3s2ikrplgos_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[inference_router] omlx 不健康，自动降级到 deepseek\ncold call: ok=False, dur=0.5s, err=provider"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":774,"aggregated":"[inference_router] omlx 不健康，自动降级到 deepseek\ncold call: ok=False, dur=0.5s, err=provider","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776049853802}}
{"type":"message","id":"cb4e15cc","parentId":"f15a1afd","timestamp":"2026-04-13T03:11:31.439Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the health check is saying omlx is unhealthy, so it's falling back to deepseek. But omlx is actually healthy (the direct test worked). The problem is that the `get_health_status()` in the inference function is checking a cached result that's stale.\n\nLooking at the `inference` function in `inference_router.py`:\n```python\nif provider in (\"gotdx\", \"omlx\"):\n    status = get_health_status(provider)\n    if status is False or (isinstance(status, dict) and not any(status.values())):\n```\n\nThe `get_health_status(provider)` returns a `bool` (True/False). \n\nSo when it returns False, the condition triggers the fallback. The health check sets `_health_status = {\"gotdx\": False, \"omlx\": True}` based on the actual test results, but then `get_health_status(\"omlx\")` is somehow returning False instead of the True that was stored, which doesn't make sense if the health check actually ran successfully. there's a thread safety issue where `get_health_lock` acquires the lock but then tries to access `_health_status` after it's already been released, creating a race condition where the status dict could be modified between the lock release and the return statement. the health status is showing `False` because the health check runs asynchronously in the background after initialization, so by the time the first inference call happens, the cached status might be stale or uninitialized. The inference function is correctly detecting that the cached status is a dict rather than a boolean and triggering the fallback to deepseek, but I need to verify whether the status is actually being refreshed properly between calls. status returned by `get_health_status(\"omlx\")` is actually a dict `{\"gotdx\": False, \"omlx\": True}`, not a bool. Let me trace through:\n\nIn `inference`:\n```python\nif provider in [\"gotdx\", \"omlx\"]:\n    status = get_health_status(provider)  # returns dict or bool\n    if status is False or (isinstance(status, dict) and not any(status.values())):\n```\n\nIf `get_health_status(\"omlx\")` returns `{\"gotdx\": False, \"omlx\": True}`, then `isinstance(status, dict)` is True, and `any(status.values())` is True, so the condition is False and no fallback happens.\n\nBut the message says \"omlx 不健康，自动降级到 deepseek\". This means the condition evaluated to True, which means either `status is False` or `any(status.values())` is False. The only way `any(status.values())` is False is if ALL values are falsy. So the health check must have returned something like `{\"gotdx\": False, \"omlx\": False}`.\n\nI think the issue is that `is_healthy` is returning a dict instead of a bool. The health status should only contain booleans, but somewhere it's getting populated with the status dict itself, causing the fallback logic to trigger incorrectly. I'm realizing the issue might be in how the lock is handled—if `_health_status` is being modified or read inconsistently between threads, the dict could get into a bad state where `is_healthy` returns something unexpected. Let me trace through what happens when the lock is acquired and released to see if there's a race condition causing the health status to become corrupted. I see the issue now - `is_healthy()` acquires the health lock, checks if data is stale, and if so calls `_run_health_checks()` which itself tries to acquire the lock again. Since the lock isn't reentrant, this causes a deadlock. I need to restructure this to avoid the nested lock acquisition.\n\nThe simplest approach is to add a `force_refresh` parameter to `is_healthy()` so callers can bypass the stale check if they've already verified the data is fresh, or I could use a separate lock just for the health check status and only acquire it when actually updating. I'm considering using an atomic compare-and-swap pattern instead, where I store the health status along with a timestamp and expiration flag, so I can check if the cache is stale without needing a lock on every call. But that's getting complicated. The simpler solution is to just accept that if health data is older than the check interval, I'll trigger a refresh synchronously on the next call—it's not perfect but it's good enough for most cases.","thinkingSignature":"2d97a94d12aeb07a25147407b5cf057452f91ad027f5678a836676dbcc02f5fa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4c10b3xmyjyt_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/AI-RXC/services/inference_router.py","edits":[{"oldText":"    def is_healthy(self, source: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"检查指定数据源是否健康\"\"\"\n        with self._health_lock:\n            stale = (time.time() - self._last_health_check) > self._health_check_interval\n        if stale:\n            return self._run_health_checks()\n        status = self.get_health_status()\n        return status.get(source, False)","newText":"    def is_healthy(self, source: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"检查指定数据源是否健康，缓存过期则同步刷新\"\"\"\n        with self._health_lock:\n            stale = (time.time() - self._last_health_check) > self._health_check_interval\n            if stale:\n                # 缓存过期，同步刷新（不在锁内调，用嵌套锁会有问题）\n                pass\n            else:\n                return self._health_status.get(source, False)\n        # 走到这里说明stale=True，刷新后重查\n        self._run_health_checks()\n        with self._health_lock:\n            return self._health_status.get(source, False)"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":79993,"output":1217,"cacheRead":35206,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116416,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776049853821,"responseId":"062b91beff5a9a9e0fd4b4811ee24e3b"}}
