{"type":"message","id":"477e6854","parentId":"9f603c45","timestamp":"2026-04-13T03:11:56.555Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me look at the `get_health_status` and `_run_health_checks` in `data_source_manager.py` to understand the thread safety issue.\n\nThe problem is:\n1. `_run_health_checks()` acquires `_health_lock`, then sets `_health_status` \n2. `get_health_status()` acquires `_health_lock`, checks if stale, if stale calls `_run_health_checks()` which tries to acquire `_health_lock` again → deadlock!\n\nThe fix: `is_healthy()` should not call `get_health_status()` if stale (since `get_health_status` would call `_run_health_checks` inside the lock → deadlock). Instead, `is_healthy` should directly check staleness and refresh synchronously outside the lock.","thinkingSignature":"2791570e239ddb6046d69b4867727e5ccdb681681b0cbc9dfa69546b5282a1c2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2ks2wwqz7b8z_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/AI-RXC/data_source_manager.py","edits":[{"oldText":"    def is_healthy(self, source: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"检查指定数据源是否健康\"\"\"\n        status = self.get_health_status()\n        return status.get(source, False)","newText":"    def is_healthy(self, source: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"检查指定数据源是否健康，缓存过期则同步刷新（避免在锁内调_run_health_checks死锁）\"\"\"\n        with self._health_lock:\n            stale = (time.time() - self._last_health_check) > self._health_check_interval\n            if not stale:\n                return self._health_status.get(source, False)\n        # 缓存过期，锁外同步刷新\n        self._run_health_checks()\n        with self._health_lock:\n            return self._health_status.get(source, False)"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":82090,"output":398,"cacheRead":35206,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117694,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timesta