{"type":"message","id":"078126e8","parentId":"74ec1f93","timestamp":"2026-04-13T03:13:08.053Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"oMLX is returning `ok=False` very quickly (0.2s). This means the oMLX call itself is failing fast. Let me check what's happening by looking at the error.\n\nThe fact that it's `ok=False` with `duration=0.2s` suggests the call failed immediately, not a timeout. Let me check what error is being returned.\n\nLet me also check - maybe the issue is that the `temperature` in `call_llm` for `omlx` provider is 0 (default from the call_llm function). Let me trace the actual error by adding more debug output.\n\nActually, let me look at how `call_llm` works with the `omlx` provider. \n\nThe `temperature=0.05` is being passed from the task config, but maybe `call_llm` has its own default temperature that overrides it, or the omlx provider's timeout is too short. Let me test the omlx provider directly to see what error is actually being returned.","thinkingSignature":"ee3ba0b3ccb513868115a304472981d8706f20ea8d3d4a2a10e2601f4b03bce6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_054zuxr6wxs0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec agentsstock1 python3 -c \"\nimport sys, time\nsys.path.insert(0, '/app')\nfrom services.llm_router import call_llm\n\nt0 = time.time()\nresult = call_llm(\n    provider='omlx',\n    model='OmniCoder-9B-Instruct-4bit',\n    messages=[{'role':'user','content':'判断：茅台涨跌是否超过2%？只答是或否。'}],\n    temperature=0.05,\n    max_tokens=512,\n    timeout_config={'total': 60},\n)\nprint('ok:', result.get('ok'))\nprint('duration:', time.time()-t0)\nprint('error_type:', result.get('error_type'))\nprint('error_msg:', result.get('error_message','')[:200])\nprint('text:', result.get('text','')[:100])\n\" 2>&1 | grep -v \"INFO\\|WARNING\\|account\\|mac\\|失效\\|建议\\|配置\\|临时\\|游客\\|旅客\\|THS\\|✅ TCP\\|断开\\|连接\"","timeout":90}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","us