{"type":"message","id":"f457a6a5","parentId":"b2a8ba36","timestamp":"2026-04-13T08:16:05.072Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the structure. The `dual_factor_profile` feature flag can be set to \"off\", \"default\", \"conservative\", etc. Currently it's \"off\" everywhere.\n\nFor \"正式集成\" (formal integration), I need to:\n1. Change `dual_factor_profile` from \"off\" to \"conservative\" in the live trading config\n\nBut the question is which config file to change. Since this is the real trading/live system, I should probably update `live_trading_v1.json`.\n\nHowever, I should first understand the current shadow pipeline. The shadow pipeline generated the `dual_factor_shadow_*_live_payload.json` which contains the signals. For formal integration, the system would use the dual factor signals directly instead of the baseline combo.\n \nI need to be cautious here—this is a trading system, so formal integration means replacing the current live signals with the dual factor version. I should clarify with the user which config they want to update: `live_trading_v1.json` for the main live system, or one of the paper trading configs for simulation. Looking at the structure, `live_trading_v1.json` appears to be the primary production config.\n\nBefore making changes, I should also understand what the conservative profile actually does and whether there's a staged rollout approach like a feature flag to test it first.","thinkingSignature":"5b2bd869ecb4ab1e9ec6d7afb6eaae9205b2db06973bd29a2d5ca63493ea2134"},{"type":"text","text":"明白了！当前 `dual_factor_profile` 在所有配置里都是 `\"off\"`。正式集成需要将它切换到 `\"conservative\"`。在改之前确认一下：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f6jsrewtzj6s_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"DUAL_FACTOR_VALID_PROFILES\\|dual_factor_profile.*conservative\\|integration_mode\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/runtime_date_utils.py | head -15","timeout"