{"type":"message","id":"6cabb0f0","parentId":"f657c91f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:21:36.738Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so there are multiple issues:\n\n1. The `live_system_v1_20260413.json` was successfully generated (reached combo_v1 section)\n2. But then the merged signals generation failed with: `\"reason\": \"materialize_signal_chain_failed\"` and a Python error: `'set' object has no attribute 'index'`\n3. The `daily_basic_trade_date` is still `20260407` (lagging 6 days from the target 20260413)\n\nWait - the Tushare data was updated to 20260410 last time. But `market_trade_date: 20260413`? The price history was updated but the `daily_basic_all` file is still at 20260407. \n\nThe `basic_lag_days: 6` confirms the daily_basic file is outdated, though the price data appears current. The immediate blocker is that `'set' object has no attribute 'index'` error in the live candidate generation. Let me trace where this error originates in the code.","thinkingSignature":"e2c4cf6feb3748c9f2f7d4ed17364d62f97d6c4b126d7b8926b957dbdea08d0d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p67grsjnlkzg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"\\.index\\|set.*object\\|has no attribute\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/prepare_live_signal_tickets.py 2>/dev/null | head -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54711,"output":294,"cacheRead":35406,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90411,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776072077141,"responseId":"062be88d3a5e290e17bf23424a066252"}}
