{"type":"message","id":"1fbe5007","parentId":"09a50d8e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:21:46.234Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is probably from within the generate_live_candidates script, which is called by prepare_live_signal_tickets.py. Let me look at the `generate_live_candidates` step.\n\nActually, wait. Looking at the error more carefully:\n```json\n\"reason\": \"'set' object has no attribute 'index'\",\n\"price_lag_days\": 0,\n\"basic_lag_days\": 6\n```\n\nThe `price_lag_days: 0` means the price data (a_stock_history.csv) is current (has 20260413 data). \n\nBut `basic_lag_days: 6` means the daily_basic file is still stale (only has data up to 20260407). This is the same root cause - the Tushare `daily_basic` data needs to be refreshed too. The download_tushare.py script updates price data but the `daily_basic` is a separate file. Let me check what the download_tushare.py does for daily_basic.","thinkingSignature":"eee64992325791ef27ee5f420d5924162faa52d5c565acdd3f837c0659d38f00"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fwyx2a2j8mmm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"daily_basic\\|basic\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/download_tushare.py | head -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":55023,"output":264,"cacheRead":35406,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90693,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776072096786,"responseId":"062be8a0b6f7adcda080558de7cdc3f0"}}
