{"type":"message","id":"d9ab2291","parentId":"675a5a73","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:24:30.289Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error happens in `apply_stock_analysis_overlay`. This is calling another script. But more importantly, this whole signal chain is complex and requires fresh daily_basic data.\n\nLet me take a completely different approach. Instead of trying to fix all these interdependent scripts, let me understand what the actual minimal fix is:\n\n**The core problem**: balanced and aggressive portfolios need to be regenerated for date 20260413.\n\n**The blocking issues**:\n1. daily_basic is stale (only up to 20260407)\n2. The paper order generation script has Arrow dtype bugs with pandas 2.0+\n\n**Quickest fix approach**: \n- Fix the daily_basic download issue (separate script or extend download_tushare.py)\n\n\n- Fix the Arrow dtype issue in prepare_paper_orders_v1.py\n\nActually, the simplest path forward is to bypass the stale data checks entirely. Since the issue mentions停留20260330, I should check if the existing paper orders from that date can be copied to 20260413 instead of regenerating everything from scratch.\n\nBut that's not a real solution. What I really need to do is tackle both blockers: add a daily_basic refresh function to download_tushare.py, then fix the dtype problem in prepare_paper_orders_v1.py. For the dtype fix, the issue is that some columns are being set as strings but then receiving integer values, so I need to find where this mismatch happens and ensure consistent typing throughout.","thinkingSignature":"483d17dc6f6030fab5c1e7ce9e52a0bc1dd87d7a9ea3ad27245ae8bc237174d7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xlvqca711g5m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"df\\[.*at\\[.*\\]\\|out\\.at\\|setitem_column\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/apply_risk_to_merged_signals.py 2>/dev/null | head -10","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messa