{"type":"message","id":"efccb1ef","parentId":"0a00637f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T13:19:38.848Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No symlinks in the output means no symlinks to worry about. The issue might be something else - maybe a very deep directory structure. Let me look at the `walkDirectory` function more carefully.","thinkingSignature":"2bb20f6e1fd29ac3d1f52f517724e1859af89911a77b17ca52696fe0791210d6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fxqjxq65415y_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '196,240p' ~/.openclaw/skills/auto-backup-openclaw-user-data/scripts/backup.js","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":103636,"output":102,"cacheRead":35406,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":139144,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776086374214,"responseId":"062c20668995d052ccc1623ce495306e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"28f7063f","parentId":"efccb1ef","timestamp":"2026-04-13T13:19:38.895Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fxqjxq65415y_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"async walkDirectory(dirPath, excludeDirs, excludePatterns, relativeBase) {\n    const files = [];\n    const openclawRoot = OPENCLAW_ROOT;\n    \n    async function walk(currentPath, self) {\n      try {\n        const entries = await fs.readdir(currentPath, { withFileTypes: true });\n        \n        for (const entry of entries) {\n          const fullPath = path.join(currentPath, entry.name);\n          const relativePath = relativeBase \n            ? path.join(relativeBase, path.relative(dirPath, fullPath))\n            : path.relative(openclawRoot, fullPath);\n          \n          // 检查是否在排除目录中\n          if (excludeDirs.includes(entry.name)) {\n            continue;\n          }\n          \n          // 检查是否匹配排除模式\n          if (excludePatterns.some(pattern => this.matchPattern(entry.name, pattern))) {\n            continue;\n          }\n          \n          if (entry.isDirectory()) {\n            await walk.call(self, fullPath, self);\n          } else if (entry.isFile()) {\n            // 检查文件是否可读\n            try {\n              await fs.access(fullPath, fs.constants.R_OK);\n              files.push({\n                path: fullPath,\n                relativePath: relativePath\n              });\n            } catch (accessErr) {\n              if (accessErr.code === 'EBUSY') {\n                // 文件被占用，跳过\n                continue;\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      } catch (err) {\n        // 忽略无法访问的目录\n      }"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":12,"aggregated":"async walkDirectory(dirPath, excludeDirs, excludePatterns, relativeBase) {\n    const files = [];\n    const openclawRoot = OPENCLAW_ROOT;\n    \n    async function walk(currentPath, self) {\n      try {\n        const entries = await fs.readdir(currentPath, { withFileTypes: true });\n        \n        for (const entry of entries) {\n          const fullPath = path.join(currentPath, entry.name);\n          const relativePath = relativeBase \n            ? path.join(relativeBase, path.relative(dirPath, fullPath))\n            : path.relative(openclawRoot, fullPath);\n          \n          // 检查是否在排除目录中\n          if (excludeDirs.includes(entry.name)) {\n            continue;\n          }\n          \n          // 检查是否匹配排除模式\n          if (excludePatterns.some(pattern => this.matchPattern(entry.name, pattern))) {\n            continue;\n          }\n          \n          if (entry.isDirectory()) {\n            await walk.call(self, fullPath, self);\n          } else if (entry.isFile()) {\n            // 检查文件是否可读\n            try {\n              await fs.access(fullPath, fs.constants.R_OK);\n              files.push({\n                path: fullPath,\n                relativePath: relativePath\n              });\n            } catch (accessErr) {\n              if (accessErr.code === 'EBUSY') {\n                // 文件被占用，跳过\n                continue;\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      } catch (err) {\n        // 忽略无法访问的目录\n      }","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776086378882}}
{"type":"message","id":"7577edb6","parentId":"28f7063f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T13:19:48.891Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - there's no protection against circular symlinks. macOS has a lot of `.Trash`, `.DocumentRevisions-V100`, and similar directories that could cause deep recursion. Also, there could be a symlink loop. Let me check if there are any symlinks to directories.\n\nActually, the issue might be that `entry.isDirectory()` returns true for symlinks to directories, which then get walked into, potentially creating infinite loops. Let me add some exclusions and also check for symlinks.\n\nLooking at the exclude list in our config: `[\"logs\", \"cache\", \"tmp\", \"node_modules\", \"backups\", \".git\"]`. \n\nThe main problem is that the node.js script is running as a background process and running out of stack. The issue might be with very deep directory structures or circular symlinks. Let me add more exclusions to the config file, specifically for macOS system directories that might be linked.","thinkingSignature":"c5e2eb9a1982fc8fc02fe925d5458a57afc6984cbd87e1b9726056ba673379c4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jbs9z9qb2og8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/ | head -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":104064,"output":238,"cacheRead":35406,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":139708,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776086378898,"responseId":"062c206b2b65c4b3e0d20b254c82373c"}}
