{"type":"message","id":"e9bd4a38","parentId":"b35c2490","timestamp":"2026-04-13T13:20:45.161Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so:\n- quant_projects: 1.2G\n- memory: 1.0G\n- Others might be large too\n\nBut 16GB total and it's failing with stack overflow after 10 seconds. The issue is probably the walk going into very deep directory structures (node_modules, .git objects, etc.) even with exclusions. The exclude list only matches `node_modules` by name, not path.\n\nLet me update the config to exclude more directories by adding specific path exclusions, and also increase the max depth if possible. But first, let me check if there's a way to exclude by pattern in the skill.\n\nActually, looking at the `walkDirectory` function - it checks `excludeDirs.includes(entry.name)` where `excludeDirs` comes from `this.config.backup.exclude`. So `node_modules` should work if it's in the list.\n\n\nBut I wonder if the walk is actually traversing into those directories before the filter gets applied. The real problem could be circular symlinks or just an enormous number of nested folders. Let me check whether `entry.isDirectory()` returns true for symlinks pointing to directories - if so, the walk would keep following them without catching the exclusion.","thinkingSignature":"f9cb96d9edf8077a48dd50a4f10e278426d0e05629f0d9bf1232f63525fd26e3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6453tpflpbky_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\ncontent = open('/Users/ling/.openclaw/skills/auto-backup-openclaw-user-data/scripts/backup.js').read()\n\n# Fix: add symlink check to prevent circular references\nold = '''if (entry.isDirectory()) {\n            await walk.call(self, fullPath, self);'''\n\nnew = '''if (entry.isDirectory() && !entry.isSymbolicLink()) {\n            await walk.call(self, fullPath, self);'''\n\nif old in content:\n    content = content.replace(old, new)\n    open('/Users/ling/.openclaw/skills/auto-backup-openclaw-user-data/scripts/backup.js', 'w').write(content)\n    print('fixed symlink recursion')\nelse:\n    print('not found')\nPYEOF","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":106099,"output":440,"cacheRead":35406,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":141945,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776086429353,"responseId":"062c209dd1ecf79df702021f0114e9de"}}
